The '''[[2009 NFL season|2009]] [[Kansas City Chiefs]] season''' will be the franchise's 50th season, and fourth with head coach [[Herman Edwards]] at the helm. A new general manager will be hired to replace [[Carl Peterson]], who resigned effective the end of the 2008 season. The Chiefs will attempt to improve on their 2-14 record from [[2008 Kansas City Chiefs season|2008]] with the third overall selection in the [[2009 NFL Draft]].
